Solve my problem. It stemmed from a misunderstanding of how RXJS was working. An [issue][1] on the RxJS github page gave me the answer. Each subscriptions causes the observable pipeline to be re-evaluated. By adding the `share` operator to the pipeline it resolves this behavior.

    export default update$.pipe(
        scan(
          (state, updater) =&gt; 
            updater(state),
          Record(initial)()
        ),
        share()
      );


